===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[escadron]]'', formerly also ''[[esquadron]]'', or {{It.}} ''[[squadrone]]''.  See [[squad]].

===Noun===
'''squadron'''
# {{dated}}: Primarily, a square; hence, a square body of troops; a body of troops drawn up in a square.
#:''"Those half-rounding quards Just met, and, closing, stood in '''squadron''' joined."''  -Milton.
# ''(Army):'' A body of cavalry comparising two companies or troops, and averging from one hundred and twenty to two hundred men.
# ''(Navy):'' A detachment of vessels employed on any particular service or station, under the command of the senior officer; as, the North Atlantic Squadron.
# ''(Air Force):'' A [[tactical]] [[air force]] [[unit]]; consists of at least two [[flight]]s; multiple squadrons make up a [[group]]

